Released under the Saregama label,<ref name = "Part 1">{{cite web | url=http://www.saregama.com/portal/pages/film?mode=get_album_info&albumId=1149 | title=Saregama Album Details : Anbe Vaa - Page 1 | work=[[Saregama]] | accessdate=27 November 2014 | archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141127043132/http://www.saregama.com/portal/pages/film?mode=get_album_info&albumId=1149 | archivedate=27 November 2014}}</ref><ref name = "Part 2">{{cite web | url=http://www.saregama.com/portal/pages/film?mode=get_album_info&albumId=1149&ppvAlbumId=0&curPage=2 | title=Saregama Album Details : Anbe Vaa - Page 2 | work=[[Saregama]] | accessdate=27 November 2014 | archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141127043424/http://www.saregama.com/portal/pages/film?mode=get_album_info&albumId=1149&ppvAlbumId=0&curPage=2 | archivedate=27 November 2014}}</ref> the film's [[Original soundtrack|soundtrack]] and [[background music|score]] were composed by [[M. S. Viswanathan]], while the lyrics were written by [[Vaali (poet)|Vaali]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://play.raaga.com/tamil/album/anbe-vaa-t0000025|title=Anbe Vaa|publisher=[[Raaga.com]]|accessdate=26 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141126045247/http://play.raaga.com/tamil/album/anbe-vaa-t0000025|archivedate=26 November 2014}}</ref> A book containing the lyrics of the film's songs was also released.<ref name = "Sylvian"/>

The soundtrack received positive critical reception. G. Dhananjayan, in his book ''The Best of Tamil Cinema'', said all the songs were popular, contributing to the film's success.{{sfn|Dhananjayan|2011|page=235}} Film critic [[Randor Guy]] of ''[[The Hindu]]'' called the songs "melodious", describing the soundtrack as one of the film's major positives. He said the song "Pudhiya Vaanam" had "a political touch", and was "brilliantly photographed by master lens man S. Maruthi Rao." He also called "Rajavin Paarvai" a "hit number."<ref name = "BFTP Guy"/>

Meera Ramanathan of [[Behindwoods.com]] wrote, "If he [T. M. Soundararajan] gave a mellifluous and emotionally high sibling reflection in Malarthum Malaratha in ''Pasa Malar'', he matched it with Rajavin Paarvai Rani en Pakkam in ''Anbe Vaa''."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-column/tms---golden-voice.html|title=TMS - GOLDEN VOICE|publisher=[[Behindwoods.com]]|author=Meera Ramanathan|accessdate=27 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141127044432/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-column/tms---golden-voice.html|archivedate=27 November 2014}}</ref> Another reviewer from Behindwoods.com, Rekhs, wrote that "Rajavin Paarvai [...] takes us back to not just the 60s but a time when reel life transported us to a dream world of escapism and 100% entertainment."<ref name ="Rekhs">{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-celebs-column/common-mans-king.html|title=COMMON MAN'S KING|publisher=Behindwoods.com|author=Rekhs|date=6 May 2013|accessdate=27 November 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141127083810/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-celebs-column/common-mans-king.html|archivedate=27 November 2014}}</ref>

IndiaGlitz described "Naan Parthathile" as a "timeless masterpiece from TMS-MSV-Vaali combo."<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/dreamy-melodies-for-the-valentines-day-tamil-news-54446 | title=Dreamy melodies for the Valentine's Day | publisher=IndiaGlitz | date=13 February 2010 | accessdate=27 November 2014 | archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141121084608/http://www.indiaglitz.com/dreamy-melodies-for-the-valentines-day-tamil-news-54446 | archivedate=21 November 2014}}</ref> Regarding "Pudhiya Vaanam", IndiaGlitz wrote, "When we think of 'vaanam', the immediate song that pops into our head is ofcourse 'pudhiya vaanam pudhiya bhoomi'. And why this song? MGR makes a wonderful appearance and enthralls the audience. Even today there is no replacement for this song from the movie ''Anbe Vaa''. What a commanding role he has in the song!"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/vaanam-pola--tamil-news-114176 | title='Vaanam' Pola! | publisher=IndiaGlitz | date=15 September 2014 | accessdate=27 November 2014 | archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141127082819/http://www.indiaglitz.com/vaanam-pola--tamil-news-114176 | archivedate=27 November 2014}}</ref> On "Love Birds", IndiaGlitz wrote, "The first thing that hits our mind talking about birds in Tamil songs, we cannot miss 'Love birds, love birds, Thakathimitha'."<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/birds-in-songs-tamil-news-102913 | title=Birds in songs | publisher=IndiaGlitz | date=31 January 2014 | accessdate=27 November 2014 | archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20141127170812/http://www.indiaglitz.com/birds-in-songs-tamil-news-102913 | archivedate=27 November 2014}}</ref>

